  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (e05b9c7 2023-08-03T00:17:21.124122221Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge install\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen I try installing a submodule in a different root I get duplicated submodule paths. For example `forge install https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts.git --no-commit --root lib/blazeswap`  gives me a submodule path `lib/blazeswap/lib/blazeswap/lib/contracts`, when I would like it to be `lib/blazeswap/contracts`.",
